                     </author>
                     <author key="person_f3586">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Sa'di.</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9837">The Divan of Hafiz followed by the Pandnamah attributed to Sa'di and with the Bustan of Sa'di written diagonally in the margins.</title>
                     <note>F1a: scribbling, presumably defacing the name of a previous (European) owner, beside the date 1787. F1b, signature of David Price. Front flyleaf: Presented by Major Price. (In Morley's hand?) The Hafiz has the preface of Muhammad Gulandam. Ruled margins and dividing panels in red. Headings also in red.</note>
                     <incipit>Hamd u thana-yi bi-hadd wa sipas-i bi-qiyas [sic]</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>As for Codrington/Reade Nos 251 and 265.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
